# Help: XFS developer debug build
#
# Alternative to fs/xfs-advanced.config. Enables XFS_DEBUG, which
# turns on every ASSERT check, extra sanity verification in the
# metadata paths, and fatal assertion behaviour. Intended for XFS
# kernel developers chasing a specific problem; the resulting
# kernel is substantially slower and larger than a production
# build.
#
# XFS_DEBUG is mutually exclusive with XFS_WARN at the Kconfig
# level ("depends on XFS_FS && !XFS_DEBUG" on XFS_WARN), so this
# fragment supersedes fs/xfs-advanced.config's XFS_WARN when both
# are present in the same merge (last-wins: if xfs-debug is after
# xfs-advanced on the merge command line, XFS_DEBUG=y is written
# and olddefconfig forces XFS_WARN to n). XFS_DEBUG_EXPENSIVE
# layers on the costlier checks; XFS_ASSERT_FATAL (default y in
# Kconfig when XFS_DEBUG is set) is set explicitly for clarity.
#
# The feature bools (XFS_QUOTA, XFS_RT, XFS_ONLINE_SCRUB,
# XFS_ONLINE_SCRUB_STATS, XFS_ONLINE_REPAIR) are intentionally not
# restated here; layer fs/xfs-advanced.config first if you want
# those on alongside debug.
#
# All symbols are bool and parent on tristate XFS_FS, which Kconfig
# permits with XFS_FS=m. XFS_FS is inlined so this fragment composes
# on the base alone. No builtin/ counterpart is needed.
# See: fs/xfs/Kconfig
# See: https://docs.kernel.org/filesystems/xfs/index.html

#
# Inlined prerequisite (fs/xfs.config)
#
CONFIG_XFS_FS=m
CONFIG_XFS_POSIX_ACL=y

CONFIG_XFS_DEBUG=y
CONFIG_XFS_DEBUG_EXPENSIVE=y
CONFIG_XFS_ASSERT_FATAL=y
